    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1927-07-25T10:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1927-07-25T10:00:00-05:00" n="125"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d125">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">500.A15 a 1/475: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                        Chairman of the American Delegation</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Gibson</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Paraphrase]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1927-07-25T11:00:00-04:00">
                            <hi rend="italic">July 25, 1927—11 a.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>61. Your No. 115, July 23, 2 p.m. I observe no particular objection to first
                    political clause if necessity arises for it. In view of long <pb facs="0219"
                        n="133" xml:id="pg_133"/> distance the Japanese have to travel and time
                    required by both countries to prepare for conference it might be well that 6
                    months’ notice be required before any meeting called under this clause be held;
                    or, the clause might be made a part of general revision clause of the
                    treaty.</p>
                <p rend="center">. . . . . . . . . . . . . .</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Kellogg</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
